column5: I will be celebrating by fishing for the day  hope everyone enjoys the day..  and  O Canada
Happy Canada Day for sure Terry  No other place in the world I'd rather be
Take a little time today to think of what we have as a nation. Look at world history and world news....yes, we are blessed indeed. I know I'm privileged. Have a happy and safe Canada Day everyone.
Happy Canada Day.  The Firefighters in my town put on quite a little event every year.  I am taking my wife and little boy down to it.
Wishing my northern neighbors a great holiday  I've spent many a Canada Day's in the past while fishing Rice Lake and it was always a blast.
HAPPY CANADA DAY to all!!!!!! Will also be my unofficial bass opener, this afternoon/evening!!
Happy Birthday to the greatest country in the world to live in.  I wish everyone a fun and safe Canada Day and have a great long weekend!!
happy Canada day to all.  Extra special for our family always, landed here 51years ago ago today and with great pleasure made a contribution to the growth of this great nation.  I'm going golfing.
Happy Canada to, all enjoy and be safe.
same  have fun and be safe all
Happy Canada day to all, We had the niece over but missed the east york parade. I bit of a bummer but the rest of the day should go well.
Good stuff Geoff.  We're heading out soon.  Hopefully one of us can get an upgrade for the team!
Happy Canada Day Terry!!!  Enjoying the lovely weather today
Happy Canada Day.  Thanks for letting us in to enjoy your great fishing and wilderness.
right now, only if rock bass count...      but the kids are having fun.
Happy CANADA DAY to all my friends up north.  Great three-day week-end for fishing and hope to see lots of pics early next week.
